MSMEs are the engine of ASEAN’s economy—making up 97% of businesses, contributing to an estimated 45% of GDP, and employing millions across the region.
The “AI for MSME Advancement in ASEAN” (AIM ASEAN) project, a two-year initiative led by the [ASEAN Foundation](https://id.linkedin.com/company/asean-foundation?trk=public_post-text) in partnership with the AI Opportunity Fund: Asia-Pacific, an initiative by AVPN, supported by [Google](https://www.linkedin.com/company/google?trk=public_post-text).org and [Asian Development Bank (ADB)](https://ph.linkedin.com/company/asian-development-bank?trk=public_post-text). The initiative aims to empower 100,000 MSMEs across all 10 ASEAN Member States with hands-on AI skills. More than training, it’s about building a sustainable ecosystem where small businesses can thrive in the AI era.
Together, we’re building an AI-enabled ASEAN, where small businesses lead the way in driving innovation, resilience, and growth.
